         <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn" rendition="class:83225 maturity:83209">
             <p><lb n="1"/><unclear>p</unclear><supplied reason="lost">o</supplied>kuḍurakasa mah<unclear>i</unclear>s<unclear>eka</unclear>sa vi<unclear>ma</unclear>la<supplied reason="lost">sa dānaṁ</supplied> paṭo</p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
             <listApp>
                 <app loc="1">
                     <lem>mah<unclear>i</unclear>s<unclear>eka</unclear>sa vi<unclear>ma</unclear>la<supplied reason="lost">sa dānaṁ</supplied></lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Nakanishi+Hinuber2014_01">mah<unclear>i</unclear>s<supplied reason="lost">eka</supplied>sa va <gap reason="lost" quantity="2" unit="character"/> la<supplied reason="lost">sa deyadhama</supplied></rdg>
                     <note>The name Vimala is attested in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Tsukamoto1996_01"/><citedRange unit="item">Sanc 225</citedRange></bibl>. There is only the space for three missing <foreign>akṣaras</foreign> between the preserved <foreign>la</foreign> and the <foreign>pa</foreign>, so the reconstruction <foreign>dānaṁ</foreign> seems preferable to <foreign>deyadhama</foreign>.</note>
                 </app>
             </listApp>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" resp="part:vito">
             <p>A slab: the gift of Vimala from Pokuḍura, from the Mahisa <supplied reason="explanation">country</supplied>.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
             <p>On the place name Pokuḍura, see also <ref target="DHARMA_INSKnI00057.xml">KnI 67</ref>.</p>
         </div>
